"{\"uid\": \"thetelegraphandargus.co.uk-news-24483204.cyclist-strong-bradford-links-wins-gold-paris-olympics-dramatic-style\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"2024 Paris Olympic GamesCyclingPeopleSportBradfordOtley  A CYCLIST with strongBradfordlinks\\u00a0\\u00a0stormed back from a puncture to take a second consecutive Olympic mountain bike gold in dramatic fashion at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Pidcock's\\u00a0race was in danger of unravelling when he suffered a flat front tyre on the fourth of eight laps, shortly after he had taken control of the 35km race with an attack which split the pack.\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 219, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having fallen 40 seconds behind French hope Victor Koretzky, theOtleyracer,\\u00a0who was once a key member of the Bradford-based Paul Milnes team, fought his way back to reclaim the lead with a lap and a half to go, but the pair traded blows in the last couple of kilometres - dramatically touching wheels - before\\u00a0Pidcock\\u00a0burst forward to take the win.\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 453, \"end\": 459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9585003510030191, \"rank\": 0.029824626270155776, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"score\": 0.9999880939516794, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Koretzky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock\\u00a0was booed by the home crowds at Elancourt Hill, who had been ecstatic when Koretzky had attacked on the final climb of the race - the sort of territory where\\u00a0Pidcock\\u00a0would be expected to make a move - to take the lead late on.\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 811, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elancourt\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But their hearts would be broken after\\u00a0Pidcock\\u00a0got his nose in front of Koretzky as the path narrowed before a tree, the decisive moment in a tense race.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking to the BBC following his win, Pidcock said: \\\"I wanted to show what sport is all about - never giving up.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1178, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.5836691713451123, \"rank\": 0.452182239861849, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is a shame the French were booing me.\\\"\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1296, \"end\": 1302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9585003510030191, \"rank\": 0.029824626270155776, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added: \\\"It is super nice that they are all here (his family).\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not thank everybody enough.\\\"\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock with his gold medal on the podium(Image: Martin Rickett)After a relatively poor start,\\u00a0Pidcock\\u00a0had moved to the front on the third lap and then took control, only for things to unravel with a front flat tyre.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1473, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"score\": 0.9998596731994353, \"rank\": 0.00014027755404834167, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock\\u00a0was lucky in that it happened close to the pits but his team were not ready for him and it was a slow change, leading\\u00a0Pidcock\\u00a0down in ninth place, the gap to the front suddenly ballooning.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He caught back up to catch Koretzky with two laps to go, but the effort told as he could not shake off the Frenchman until the very last.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is only 16 days since\\u00a0Pidcock\\u00a0pulled out of the Tour de France suffering from Covid.\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The reigning mountain bike world champion had made this race his number one target all season, and his determination to deliver showed in the final two laps of a pulsating contest.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This website and associated newspapers adhere to the Independent Press Standards Organisation's     Editors' Code of Practice.\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you have a complaint 